A short summary of the past year of the hostiles for the Ukrainian working class

Negative effects:
▪️destroyed country — the amount of direct documented damage to the infrastructure of Ukraine is 137.8 billion dollars;
▪️destroyed industry — the fall in real production reached an average of 70%;
▪️the economy is on the verge of collapse — the country has collapsed into a debt hole for the next 50-60 years. Ukraine's real GDP has decreased by about 30%, and the public debt is 3.434 trillion hryvnias;
▪️hryvnia continues to depreciate — inflation is at the level of 26%;
▪️absence of work — the unemployment rate in Ukraine is estimated at 25-26%, i.e., about 3.2 million unemployed people.
▪️mortality increased by 24%, amounting to 541,739 cases;
▪️medical infrastructure was significantly damaged — 1100 medical facilities were damaged, 144 of them were completely destroyed;
▪️the total debt of the population for housing and communal services, as well as for gas and electricity, is at least UAH 81.4 billion;
▪️17.6 million people need humanitarian assistance;
▪️almost 11 million people left the country;
▪️absence of human rights and freedom of speech — the state passes laws that curtail the rights of workers and strictly subordinate the media to the will of the ruling class of capitalists, which results in a drop in the level of trust in them among the population;
▪️the lawlessness of officials and corruption in power has only increased — the revealed facts of theft of humanitarian aid, budget theft, and corruption scandals in the Ministry of Defense and other government agencies are only the tip of the iceberg;
▪️the split of the population based on culture and language has deepened;
▪️ losses in the army are colossal but classified, although officials from the EU mentioned a figure of at least 100,000 dead;
▪️the labor movement in the country is crushed — not a single significant strike has been held throughout the year.

'Positive' for the working class:
▪️Ukraine survived as a capitalist state;
▪️in confrontation with the Russian capitalists, the ruling class of capitalists in Ukraine, not without the help of foreign capital, retained its monopoly for political power and economic power in the country;
▪️the dictatorship of the ruling class has become even more reactionary and predatory than before;
▪️the country has finally been turned into a 'banana republic', a source of cheap labor and raw materials for foreign capital, as well as a field of struggle and redistribution of spheres of influence between the imperialist powers.

